line_2: 'That's not the Price of empty Songs,

line_1: No guilt so black as thine belongs,
line_2: Which loads my length'ning years with wrongs.

line_1: And all the Frolicks which to Wine belongs.
line_2: And in carouzing with lascivious Songs,

line_1: Assert an empire which to ALL belongs,
line_2: And vindicate a world's long suffer'd wrongs.

line_1: Let Man the vict'ry bless, its prize to Man belongs.
line_2: And pour to Liberty exulting songs,

line_1: Scarcely an ill to human life belongs,
line_2: But what our follies cause, or mutual wrongs;

line_1: The Praise that to thy Name belongs
line_2: In blessing Thee with grateful Songs
